# Visit Counts System Documentation

## Overview
This portfolio now uses a hybrid storage system that stores visit counts directly in the HTML file and localStorage for persistence across browsers.

## Current Visit Counts
- **speechy-pop**: 9 visits
- **marketing-plan**: 4 visits  
- **crypto-bot**: 34 visits

## How It Works

### 1. HTML Storage
- **Hidden Input Fields**: Counts are stored in hidden `<input>` elements in the HTML
- **Real-time Updates**: Counts update immediately when links are clicked
- **Persistent Storage**: Counts are saved in the HTML file itself

### 2. Backup Storage
- **localStorage**: Browser-based backup storage
- **Cross-session**: Counts persist between browser sessions
- **Fallback**: Works if HTML storage fails

### 3. Display System
- **Link Counters**: Shows "(visited: X times)" next to each project link
- **Live Panel**: Fixed position panel showing current counts
- **Real-time Updates**: All displays update simultaneously

## Storage Locations

### Hidden Input Fields (in HTML)
```html
<input type="hidden" id="speechy-pop-storage" value="9">
<input type="hidden" id="marketing-plan-storage" value="4">
<input type="hidden" id="crypto-bot-storage" value="34">
```

### Display Elements
- **Link Counters**: `speechy-pop-count`, `marketing-plan-count`, `crypto-bot-count`
- **Live Panel**: `speechy-pop-display`, `marketing-plan-display`, `crypto-bot-display`

## Benefits
✅ **HTML Storage**: Counts stored directly in the HTML file
✅ **Cross-browser**: Works on any browser/device
✅ **Real-time Updates**: Immediate count updates
✅ **Persistent**: Counts don't reset between browsers
✅ **Backup System**: localStorage as fallback

## How to Update Counts
1. Click any project link
2. Count automatically increments
3. All displays update simultaneously
4. Counts saved to localStorage
5. HTML file can be manually updated with new counts

## Manual Count Updates
To manually set counts, update the hidden input values in the HTML:
```html
<input type="hidden" id="speechy-pop-storage" value="42">
<input type="hidden" id="marketing-plan-storage" value="15">
<input type="hidden" id="crypto-bot-storage" value="8">
```

## Privacy
- No external services required
- Counts stored locally in HTML and browser
- No personal data collected
- Counts visible to all visitors
